nodes.title: Info
widgets_values:
====================
 JPS Workflow v20.5
====================

5 Generation Modes (blue nodes)
===============================

- TXT2IMG
- IMG2IMG
- Canny Control Net
- Depth Control Net
- Inpainting

Strength and Ctrl-Options are not used by TXT2IMG.

Ctrl-Options are not used by IMG2IMG and Inpainting.

Only the corresponding strength setting is used. Separate strength fields are only included for convenience when switching between modes, as different modes need quite different values.


Inpainting (see Generation Modes):
==================================

To some extend you can control how much inpainting is trying to fix the results by changing steps and base percentage. If you get artefacts on the border of the masked area try changing those values.

For Inpainting use "Open Mask Editor" in the context menu of "Generation Input Image". High "strength_percent" values (default = 100) are best for consistent Inpainting results.


Revision (brown nodes)
======================

Use images instead or in addition to text prompts. You can merge images if you use more than one input image. It's recommended to turn off text prompts for best results - use the provided switches to do that, as this is a cleaner way, than removing the text prompts manually.

The ON/OFF switch for the first image will work as master switch for this feature. So you will always have to use that input image first. If you don't want to use the feature, just turn off the first Revision Image - there's no need to return every single option to off or default.

Input images will be cropped to square aspect ratio as required by the Clip Vision model - this would happen internally anyway, but preparing the images will allow you to influence the process and choose which part of the images should be cropped (center, top, bottom, left, right). The offset value allows you to fine tune the area of cropping.

In addition all input images will be resized to the same size. You can choose between 224x224 (that's the resolution used internally by Clip Vision) or a higher resolution and select different interpolation techniques for resizing. Different settings may change the results - find optimal values for the style and content you want to create.

Detailed options are only active if the corresponding Revision switch is turned on - there is no need to return each value to default manually, if you turn off a specific input image.

If you don't like the results try to use IP Adapter instead or in addition to Revision. Both solutions are based on Clip Vision, but work in a quite different way.


IP Adapter (yellow nodes)
=========================

Use images instead or in addition to text prompts. You can merge images if you use more than one input image.

The ON/OFF switch for the first image will work as master switch for this feature. So you will always have to use that input image first. If you don't want to use the feature, just turn off the first IP-Adapter - there's no need to return every single option to off or default.

Input images will be cropped to square aspect ratio as required by the Clip Vision model - this would happen internally anyway, but preparing the images will allow you to influence the process and choose which part of the images should be cropped (center, top, bottom, left, right). The offset value allows you to fine tune the area of cropping.

In addition all input images will be resized to the same size. You can choose between 224x224 (that's the resolution used internally by Clip Vision) or a higher resolution and select different interpolation techniques for resizing. Different settings may change the results - find optimal values for the style and content you want to create.

If you use more than one input image you can choose between Batch mode and Chain mode. Only Chain mode allows you to use different weight and noise values per input image. Chain mode adds all weight values, so you have to use lower values for Chain mode. For example 4 input images with a weight of 0.2 in Chain mode will be close to 4 input images with a weight of 0.8 in Batch mode.

Detailed options are only active if the corresponding IP Adapter is turned on - there is no need to return each value to default manually, if you turn off a specific input image.

Results are best if you keep the output size close to square aspect ratio. "Extreme ratios" like 16:9 or 21:9 don't work well and may require multiple runs. You may try to combine IP Adapter with ControlNet to get better results for in those cases.


Select Output Images
====================

You can turn on/off specific out images by using the switches in the menu area. Upscaled versions need the lower resolution image as starting point. Disabling only the standard resolution will result in errors. 

A good way to use that feature is to only generate standard resolution images first and if you like the result, reuse the last seed and generate again after turning on the upscaled (2x) output images.


Prompt Styler (work in progress)
================================

Pick an artist, movie or general style and the text prompt will be extended by corresponding key words and phrases to generate images in that style.


Resolution from settings or input image
=======================================

You can switch between using your own resolution / aspect ratio and using the aspect ratio of the input image. 

For best results the size will always be adjusted to one of the recommended SDXL resolutions.


Required nodes, models and other files
======================================

All required nodes should be available through ComfyUI Manager:

* Mikey Nodes (for save and prompt)
* rgthree's ComfyUi Nodes (for output switch and better seed control)
* ComfyUI_IPAdapter_plus (for IP-Adapter)
* ComfyUI's ControlNet Auxiliary Preprocessors (for Revision)
* JPS Custom Nodes for ComfyUI

SDXL Base Model:
https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0/blob/main/sd_xl_base_1.0_0.9vae.safetensors

SDXL Refiner:
https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-refiner-1.0/blob/main/sd_xl_refiner_1.0_0.9vae.safetensors

SDXL Separate VAE:
https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/sdxl-vae/resolve/main/sdxl_vae.safetensors

Upscale Model: 
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-NMKD-Superscale

Clip Vision Models (required by Revision and IP-Adapter) - copy to ComfyUI\models\clip_vision:
https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/clip_vision_g/blob/main/clip_vision_g.safetensors (for Revision)
https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/resolve/main/sdxl_models/image_encoder/model.safetensors (for SDXL models)
https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/resolve/main/models/image_encoder/model.safetensors (for vit-h SDXL models)

IP-Adapter Models - copy to ComfyUI\custom_nodes\ComfyUI_IPAdapter_plus\models:
https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/resolve/main/sdxl_models/ip-adapter_sdxl.bin
https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/resolve/main/sdxl_models/ip-adapter_sdxl_vit-h.bin
https://huggingface.co/h94/IP-Adapter/resolve/main/sdxl_models/ip-adapter-plus_sdxl_vit-h.bin

Inpainting:
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/stable-diffusion-xl-1.0-inpainting-0.1/blob/main/unet/diffusion_pytorch_model.fp16.safetensors

Control Net:
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/controlnet-zoe-depth-sdxl-1.0/blob/main/diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors
https://huggingface.co/diffusers/controlnet-canny-sdxl-1.0/blob/main/diffusion_pytorch_model.fp16.safetensors


Additional Info
===============

It's recommended to change "Link Render Mode" in Comfy UI to "Hidden" for a better user experience, if you don't want to edit the workflow. 

You have to change some purple nodes (models, images) to your own filenames, when you first use this workflow.
